    <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
    <div class="mt-6 grid gap-12 lg:grid-cols-[1.2fr_.8fr] lg:gap-24">
      <div><h1 class="text-5xl font-medium leading-[1.02] tracking-[-.04em] sm:text-6xl">I study how software can become a better medium for thought.</h1><div class="prose-doc mt-10"><p>I’m a software developer and Computer Science / AI student interested in systems that amplify human agency. My work connects theoretical HCI research with practical engineering: local-first applications, context-aware interfaces, developer tools, and private distributed infrastructure.</p><p>Active Cognition Computing is the organizing thread. The projects documented here are laboratories—concrete attempts to test where the framework holds, where it breaks, and what it asks of software architecture.</p></div></div>
      <aside class="space-y-10 border-l border-line pl-6"><div><p class="eyebrow">Focus</p><p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-7 text-muted">Computer Science & Artificial Intelligence<br/>Human–Computer Interaction<br/>Local-first software<br/>Distributed systems</p></div><div><p class="eyebrow">Credentials</p><p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-7 text-muted">AWS & AI/ML certifications<br/>Independent systems research<br/>Open-source engineering</p></div><div><p class="eyebrow">Toolchain</p><p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-7 text-muted">Tauri · React · TypeScript<br/>Python · Vite · Ollama<br/>Systems architecture</p></div></aside>
    </div>
  </article>
